  </div>
  <span class="section-sub">Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal</span>

  <div class="lex-block">
    <span class="lex-direction">[While the priest prays silently, the Troparia and Kontakia of the liturgical day are sung by the choir. After they have been sung, the priest prays aloud:]</span>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">For holy art Thou, O our God, and unto Thee we ascribe glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto ages of ages.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label choir">Choir</span>
      <span class="lex-text">Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto the ages of ages. Amen.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="lit-subsection">
    <span class="subsection-num">The Trisagion</span>
    <h3 class="subsection-head">The Trisagion</h3>
    <span class="subsection-sub">The thrice-holy hymn of the angels</span>
    <div class="lex-block">
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
        <div class="lex-text people">
          <div class="lex-verse">
            Holy God! Holy Mighty! Holy Immortal!<br>
            Have mercy on us. <em>(3x)</em>
          </div>
          <div class="lex-verse" style="margin-top:.4rem">
            Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit,<br>
            now and ever and unto ages of ages. Amen.<br><br>
            Holy Immortal! Have mercy on us.<br>
            Holy God! Holy Mighty! Holy Immortal! Have mercy on us.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
        <span class="lex-text people">Amen.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mob-ctx-card">
    <span class="mob-ctx-tag">Trisagion</span>
    <p class="mob-ctx-body">The Trisagion, "thrice-holy," echoes the song of the Seraphim from Isaiah 6 and the vision of Revelation 4. The Church joins the angels in their eternal worship at this moment.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ VII. THE READINGS ════ -->
<section class="lit-section" id="readings" data-section="readings">
  <div class="section-watermark">VII</div>
  <span class="section-tag">Part Seven</span>
  <div class="section-head-row">
    <h2 class="section-head">The Readings</h2>
    <button class="music-btn" title="Sheet music not yet available" disabled aria-label="Sheet music (coming soon)">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="18" height="18"><path d="M12 3v10.55c-.59-.34-1.27-.55-2-.55-2.21 0-4 1.79-4 4s1.79 4 4 4 4-1.79 4-4V7h4V3h-6z"/></svg>
    </button>
  </div>
  <span class="section-sub">Prokeimenon, Epistle, and Holy Gospel</span>

  <div class="lit-subsection" style="margin-top:0;padding-top:0;border-top:none">
    <span class="subsection-num">The Prokeimenon</span>
    <h3 class="subsection-head">The Prokeimenon</h3>
    <div class="lex-block">
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Let us attend! Peace be unto all!</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label reader">Reader</span>
        <span class="lex-text">And to thy spirit!</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Wisdom!</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label reader">Reader</span>
        <span class="lex-text">The prokeimenon in the ___ tone:</span>
      </div>
      <span class="lex-direction">[Choir repeats the call from the reader three times.]</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="lit-subsection">
    <span class="subsection-num">The Epistle</span>
    <h3 class="subsection-head">The Epistle Reading</h3>
    <div class="lex-block">
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Wisdom.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label reader">Reader</span>
        <span class="lex-text">The reading is _______________.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Let us attend!</span>
      </div>
      <span class="lex-direction">[The reader chants the Epistle for the day. Upon its completion, the priest blesses the reader.]</span>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Peace be to thee.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label reader">Reader</span>
        <span class="lex-text">And to thy spirit. Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!</span>
      </div>
      <span class="lex-direction">[While the priest prays silently, the reader chants two Alleluia verses. After each one, the people respond.]</span>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
        <span class="lex-text people">Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia! <span class="lex-note">(2x)</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="lit-subsection">
    <span class="subsection-num">The Holy Gospel</span>
    <h3 class="subsection-head">The Holy Gospel</h3>
    <div class="lex-block">
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Wisdom! Let us attend. Let us listen to the Holy Gospel. Peace be unto all.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
        <span class="lex-text people">(Sung) And to your spirit!</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Let us attend.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label reader">Reader</span>
        <span class="lex-text">The reading from the Holy Gospel according to Saint _______________.</span>
      </div>
      <span class="lex-direction">[The appointed Gospel lesson is chanted by the Priest. Upon its completion, the people respond singing:]</span>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
        <span class="lex-text people">(Sung) Glory to Thee, O Lord, glory to Thee.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="lit-subsection">
    <span class="subsection-num">The Homily</span>
    <h3 class="subsection-head">The Homily</h3>
    <span class="lex-direction">[The people are invited to sit if the Homily is given. Upon completion, the people stand and prepare to sing the Litany of Fervent Supplication.]</span>
  </div>

  <div class="mob-ctx-card">
    <span class="mob-ctx-tag">The Word of God</span>
    <p class="mob-ctx-body">The Old and New Testament scriptures were originally read almost exclusively as a communal act. The services of the church remained the primary opportunity to encounter scripture for many centuries of Christian life.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ VIII. FERVENT SUPPLICATION ════ -->
<section class="lit-section" id="fervent" data-section="fervent">
  <div class="section-watermark">VIII</div>
  <span class="section-tag">Part Eight</span>
  <div class="section-head-row">
    <h2 class="section-head">Litany of Fervent<br>Supplication</h2>
    <button class="music-btn" title="Sheet music not yet available" disabled aria-label="Sheet music (coming soon)">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="18" height="18"><path d="M12 3v10.55c-.59-.34-1.27-.55-2-.55-2.21 0-4 1.79-4 4s1.79 4 4 4 4-1.79 4-4V7h4V3h-6z"/></svg>
    </button>
  </div>
  <span class="section-sub">Intensified prayer on behalf of all</span>

  <div class="lex-block">
    <span class="lex-instruct" style="margin-left:0;margin-bottom:.8rem">The people respond singing "Lord, have mercy" after each petition.</span>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Let us all say with all our soul and with all our mind, let us say.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">O Lord almighty, the God of our fathers, we pray Thee, hearken and have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Have mercy on us, O God, according to Thy great goodness, we pray Thee, hearken and have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy. <span class="lex-note">(3x)</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Again we pray for His Beatitude, our Metropolitan, Tikhon, for His Eminence, our Archbishop, Michael, for priests, deacons, and all other clergy, and for all our brethren in Christ.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy. <span class="lex-note">(3x)</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Again we pray for this country, its President, for all civil authorities, and for the armed forces.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy. <span class="lex-note">(3x)</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Again we pray for mercy, life, peace, health, salvation, and visitation for the servants of God _______________, and for the pardon and remission of their sins.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy. <span class="lex-note">(3x)</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Again we pray for those who bring offerings and do good works in this holy and all-venerable temple; for those who labor and those who sing; and for all the people here present, who await Thy great and rich mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy. <span class="lex-note">(3x)</span></span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">For Thou art a merciful God, and lovest mankind, and unto Thee we ascribe glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto ages of ages.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Amen.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="lit-subsection">
    <span class="subsection-num">The Litany for the Departed</span>
    <h3 class="subsection-head">The Litany for the Departed</h3>
    <span class="subsection-sub">Served except on Sundays and Feast Days</span>
    <div class="callout-box" style="margin-top:.5rem">
      <span class="callout-tag">Note</span>
      <p class="callout-body">The Litany for the Departed may be recited here, except on Sundays and Feast Days.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-block">
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
        <span class="lex-text priest">Again we pray for the blessed and ever-memorable holy Orthodox patriarchs; and for the blessed and ever-memorable founders of this holy church _______________; and for all our fathers and brethren, the Orthodox departed this life before us, who here and in all the world lie asleep in the Lord.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lex-exchange">
        <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
        <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy. <span class="lex-note">(3x)</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mob-ctx-card">
    <span class="mob-ctx-tag">Intensified Supplication</span>
    <p class="mob-ctx-body">Where the Great Litany responds once, this litany responds three times. The triple "Lord, have mercy" expresses deeper urgency, calling on God not as a formality, but with the full weight of the community's need.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ IX. CATECHUMENS ════ -->
<section class="lit-section" id="catechumens" data-section="catechumens">
  <div class="section-watermark">IX</div>
  <span class="section-tag">Part Nine</span>
  <div class="section-head-row">
    <h2 class="section-head">The Litany for<br>the Catechumens</h2>
    <button class="music-btn" title="Sheet music not yet available" disabled aria-label="Sheet music (coming soon)">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="18" height="18"><path d="M12 3v10.55c-.59-.34-1.27-.55-2-.55-2.21 0-4 1.79-4 4s1.79 4 4 4 4-1.79 4-4V7h4V3h-6z"/></svg>
    </button>
  </div>
  <span class="section-sub">Prayer for those preparing to enter the Church</span>

  <div class="lex-block">
    <span class="lex-instruct" style="margin-left:0;margin-bottom:.8rem">The people continue singing "Lord, have mercy" during each petition.</span>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Pray to the Lord, ye catechumens.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Let us, the faithful, pray for the catechumens, that the Lord may have mercy on them.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">That He may teach them the word of truth.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">That He may reveal to them the gospel of righteousness.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">That He may unite them to His Holy, Catholic, and Apostolic Church.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Help them, save them, have mercy on them, and keep them, O God, by Thy grace.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Bow your heads unto the Lord, ye catechumens.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">To Thee, O Lord.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">That with us they also may glorify Thine all-honorable and majestic name: of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto ages of ages.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Amen.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">All catechumens, depart. Depart, catechumens. All that are catechumens, depart. Let no catechumen remain.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mob-ctx-card">
    <span class="mob-ctx-tag">An Ancient Practice</span>
    <p class="mob-ctx-body">In earlier centuries the dismissal of catechumens was a solemn and literal act. The doors of the church were closed and guarded. The Liturgy that followed was considered so sacred that it was not to be witnessed by those not yet baptized.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ X. LITANIES OF THE FAITHFUL ════ -->
<section class="lit-section" id="faithful-litany" data-section="faithful-litany">
  <div class="section-watermark">X</div>
  <span class="section-tag">Part Ten</span>
  <div class="section-head-row">
    <h2 class="section-head">Litanies of<br>the Faithful</h2>
    <button class="music-btn" title="Sheet music not yet available" disabled aria-label="Sheet music (coming soon)">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="18" height="18"><path d="M12 3v10.55c-.59-.34-1.27-.55-2-.55-2.21 0-4 1.79-4 4s1.79 4 4 4 4-1.79 4-4V7h4V3h-6z"/></svg>
    </button>
  </div>
  <span class="section-sub">The Church prepares to offer the Holy Gifts</span>

  <div class="lex-block">
    <span class="lex-instruct" style="margin-left:0;margin-bottom:.8rem">The people continue singing "Lord, have mercy" during each petition.</span>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Again and again, in peace, let us pray to the Lord.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Wisdom. That guarded always by Thy might, we may send up glory to Thee, to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto ages of ages.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Amen.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Let us, the faithful, again and again in peace pray unto the Lord.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Lord, have mercy.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">Wisdom. For unto Thee are due all glory, honor, and worship, to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto ages of ages.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Amen.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mob-ctx-card">
    <span class="mob-ctx-tag">The Threshold</span>
    <p class="mob-ctx-body">With the catechumens departed, these two short litanies draw the congregation into final preparation for the Eucharistic offering. They mark the solemn boundary between the Liturgy of the Word and the Liturgy of the Faithful.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ XI. GREAT ENTRANCE ════ -->
<section class="lit-section" id="great-entrance" data-section="great-entrance">
  <div class="section-watermark">XI</div>
  <span class="section-tag">Part Eleven</span>
  <div class="section-head-row">
    <h2 class="section-head">The Cherubic Hymn<br><em>The Great Entrance</em></h2>
    <button class="music-btn" title="Sheet music not yet available" disabled aria-label="Sheet music (coming soon)">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="18" height="18"><path d="M12 3v10.55c-.59-.34-1.27-.55-2-.55-2.21 0-4 1.79-4 4s1.79 4 4 4 4-1.79 4-4V7h4V3h-6z"/></svg>
    </button>
  </div>
  <span class="section-sub">The procession of the Holy Gifts to the altar</span>

  <div class="callout-box">
    <span class="callout-tag">At This Time</span>
    <p class="callout-body">An offering plate is passed to the people. When the bread and wine are offered to God to be sanctified, the people in turn give their own offering.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="lex-block">
    <span class="lex-direction">[The first part of the Cherubic Hymn is sung while the Priest censes the people.]</span>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <div class="lex-text people">
        <div class="lex-verse">
          Let us who mystically represent the Cherubim,<br>
          and who sing the thrice-holy hymn<br>
          to the life-creating Trinity,<br>
          now lay aside all earthly cares.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <span class="lex-direction">[When the Priest enters the Sanctuary, the people continue singing the Cherubic Hymn. Before returning the bread and wine to the altar, the priest asks Christ to remember in His kingdom various groups of people. The last of these petitions is:]</span>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label priest">Priest</span>
      <span class="lex-text priest">You, and all Orthodox Christians, may the Lord God remember in His Kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto ages of ages.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <span class="lex-text people">Amen.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lex-exchange">
      <span class="lex-label people">People</span>
      <div class="lex-text people">
        <div class="lex-verse">
          That we may receive the King of all,<br>
          Who comes invisibly upborne by the angelic hosts.<br>
          Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mob-ctx-card">
    <span class="mob-ctx-tag">The Great Entrance</span>
    <p class="mob-ctx-body">The Great Entrance mirrors the journey of Christ to His voluntary sacrifice. The bread and wine, now carried to the altar, will become His Body and Blood. We receive the King of all.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ XII. LITANY OF SUPPLICATION ════ -->
